Note:
Runa Advanced Standard Library: JIT Profiling Module

Provides comprehensive profiling capabilities for the JIT compiler, including:
- Performance monitoring and measurement
- Bottleneck detection and analysis
- Optimization feedback and recommendations
- Memory usage profiling
- Cache performance analysis
- Compilation time tracking
- Runtime performance monitoring
- AI/agent-friendly profiling insights

Features:
- Real-time performance monitoring with minimal overhead
- Advanced bottleneck detection algorithms
- Memory usage profiling and leak detection
- Cache performance analysis and optimization
- Compilation time tracking and optimization
- Runtime performance monitoring with sampling
- AI/agent-friendly profiling insights and recommendations
- Cross-platform profiling support
:End Note

Note: Core Types and Data Structures
Type ProfilingConfig is Dictionary with:
    enabled as Boolean defaults to true
    sampling_rate as Float defaults to 0.01
    memory_profiling as Boolean defaults to true
    cache_profiling as Boolean defaults to true
    compilation_profiling as Boolean defaults to true
    runtime_profiling as Boolean defaults to true
    enable_ai_insights as Boolean defaults to true
    max_profiling_data as Integer defaults to 1000000
    metadata as Dictionary[String, Any] defaults to dictionary containing

Type ProfilingContext is Dictionary with:
    config as ProfilingConfig
    metrics as Dictionary[String, ProfilingMetric]
    samples as List[ProfilingSample]
    memory_snapshots as List[MemorySnapshot]
    cache_profiles as List[CacheProfile]
    compilation_profiles as List[CompilationProfile]
    runtime_profiles as List[RuntimeProfile]
    performance_metrics as Dictionary[String, Float]
    metadata as Dictionary[String, Any]

Type ProfilingMetric is Dictionary with:
    name as String
    value as Float
    unit as String
    timestamp as Float
    category as String
    metadata as Dictionary[String, Any]

Type ProfilingSample is Dictionary with:
    timestamp as Float
    cpu_usage as Float
    memory_usage as Float
    cache_hit_rate as Float
    compilation_time as Float
    runtime_performance as Float
    metadata as Dictionary[String, Any]

Type MemorySnapshot is Dictionary with:
    timestamp as Float
    total_memory as Integer
    used_memory as Integer
    free_memory as Integer
    heap_size as Integer
    stack_size as Integer
    allocation_count as Integer
    deallocation_count as Integer
    leak_suspicion as Float
    metadata as Dictionary[String, Any]

Type CacheProfile is Dictionary with:
    timestamp as Float
    hit_rate as Float
    miss_rate as Float
    eviction_rate as Float
    compression_ratio as Float
    cache_size as Integer
    entry_count as Integer
    average_access_time as Float
    metadata as Dictionary[String, Any]

Type CompilationProfile is Dictionary with:
    timestamp as Float
    compilation_time as Float
    optimization_time as Float
    code_generation_time as Float
    cache_lookup_time as Float
    total_instructions as Integer
    optimized_instructions as Integer
    cache_hits as Integer
    cache_misses as Integer
    metadata as Dictionary[String, Any]

Type RuntimeProfile is Dictionary with:
    timestamp as Float
    execution_time as Float
    instruction_count as Integer
    branch_count as Integer
    memory_access_count as Integer
    cache_access_count as Integer
    performance_counters as Dictionary[String, Float]
    metadata as Dictionary[String, Any]

Type ProfilingResult is:
    | ProfilingSuccess with data as Dictionary[String, Any] and insights as List[String]
    | ProfilingError with error as String and details as Dictionary[String, Any]
    | ProfilingWarning with warning as String and data as Dictionary[String, Any]

Type BottleneckAnalysis is Dictionary with:
    bottleneck_type as String
    severity as String
    location as String
    impact as Float
    recommendations as List[String]
    metadata as Dictionary[String, Any]

Type PerformanceInsight is Dictionary with:
    insight_type as String
    description as String
    impact_level as String
    confidence as Float
    recommendations as List[String]
    metadata as Dictionary[String, Any]

Note: Core Profiling Functions
Process called "create_profiling_context" that takes config as Optional[ProfilingConfig] returns ProfilingContext:
    Let default_config be ProfilingConfig with:
        enabled as true
        sampling_rate as 0.01
        memory_profiling as true
        cache_profiling as true
        compilation_profiling as true
        runtime_profiling as true
        enable_ai_insights as true
        max_profiling_data as 1000000
        metadata as dictionary containing
    
    Let final_config be config if config is not None else default_config
    
    Return ProfilingContext with:
        config as final_config
        metrics as dictionary containing
        samples as list containing
        memory_snapshots as list containing
        cache_profiles as list containing
        compilation_profiles as list containing
        runtime_profiles as list containing
        performance_metrics as dictionary containing
        metadata as dictionary containing

Process called "start_profiling" that takes context as ProfilingContext returns Boolean:
    Try:
        If not context.config.enabled:
            Return false
        
        Let start_time be get_current_time
        Set context.metadata["profiling_start_time"] to start_time
        
        If context.config.memory_profiling:
            Let memory_snapshot be take_memory_snapshot
            Add memory_snapshot to context.memory_snapshots
        
        If context.config.cache_profiling:
            Let cache_profile be take_cache_profile with context as context
            Add cache_profile to context.cache_profiles
        
        Return true
        
    Catch error:
        Return false

Process called "stop_profiling" that takes context as ProfilingContext returns ProfilingResult:
    Try:
        Let end_time be get_current_time
        Set context.metadata["profiling_end_time"] to end_time
        
        Let profiling_duration be end_time minus context.metadata["profiling_start_time"]
        
        Let analysis_result be analyze_profiling_data with context as context
        
        Let insights be list containing
        If context.config.enable_ai_insights:
            Let ai_insights be generate_ai_insights with context as context
            Add ai_insights to insights
        
        Let result_data be dictionary containing:
            "profiling_duration" as profiling_duration
            "total_samples" as length of context.samples
            "memory_snapshots" as length of context.memory_snapshots
            "cache_profiles" as length of context.cache_profiles
            "compilation_profiles" as length of context.compilation_profiles
            "runtime_profiles" as length of context.runtime_profiles
            "performance_metrics" as context.performance_metrics
        
        Return ProfilingSuccess with data as result_data and insights as insights
        
    Catch error:
        Return ProfilingError with error as error.message and details as dictionary containing

Process called "record_metric" that takes context as ProfilingContext and name as String and value as Float and unit as String and category as String returns None:
    Let current_time be get_current_time
    
    Let metric be ProfilingMetric with:
        name as name
        value as value
        unit as unit
        timestamp as current_time
        category as category
        metadata as dictionary containing
    
    Set context.metrics[name] to metric
    
    If length of context.metrics is greater than context.config.max_profiling_data:
        Let oldest_metric be find_oldest_metric with metrics as context.metrics
        Remove context.metrics[oldest_metric]

Process called "take_profiling_sample" that takes context as ProfilingContext returns None:
    If not context.config.enabled:
        Return None
    
    Let current_time be get_current_time
    
    Let cpu_usage be get_cpu_usage
    Let memory_usage be get_memory_usage
    Let cache_hit_rate be get_cache_hit_rate with context as context
    Let compilation_time be get_compilation_time with context as context
    Let runtime_performance be get_runtime_performance with context as context
    
    Let sample be ProfilingSample with:
        timestamp as current_time
        cpu_usage as cpu_usage
        memory_usage as memory_usage
        cache_hit_rate as cache_hit_rate
        compilation_time as compilation_time
        runtime_performance as runtime_performance
        metadata as dictionary containing
    
    Add sample to context.samples
    
    If length of context.samples is greater than context.config.max_profiling_data:
        Remove context.samples at index 0

Note: Memory Profiling
Process called "take_memory_snapshot" returns MemorySnapshot:
    Let current_time be get_current_time
    Let memory_info be get_memory_info
    
    Let snapshot be MemorySnapshot with:
        timestamp as current_time
        total_memory as memory_info.total_memory
        used_memory as memory_info.used_memory
        free_memory as memory_info.free_memory
        heap_size as memory_info.heap_size
        stack_size as memory_info.stack_size
        allocation_count as memory_info.allocation_count
        deallocation_count as memory_info.deallocation_count
        leak_suspicion as calculate_leak_suspicion with memory_info as memory_info
        metadata as dictionary containing
    
    Return snapshot

Process called "analyze_memory_usage" that takes context as ProfilingContext returns List[BottleneckAnalysis]:
    Let bottlenecks be list containing
    
    If length of context.memory_snapshots is less than 2:
        Return bottlenecks
    
    Let memory_trend be analyze_memory_trend with snapshots as context.memory_snapshots
    
    If memory_trend.growth_rate is greater than 0.1:
        Add BottleneckAnalysis with:
            bottleneck_type as "memory_leak"
            severity as "high" if memory_trend.growth_rate is greater than 0.5 else "medium"
            location as "heap"
            impact as memory_trend.growth_rate
            recommendations as list containing "Check for memory leaks", "Review allocation patterns"
            metadata as dictionary containing
        to bottlenecks
    
    If memory_trend.fragmentation is greater than 0.3:
        Add BottleneckAnalysis with:
            bottleneck_type as "memory_fragmentation"
            severity as "medium"
            location as "heap"
            impact as memory_trend.fragmentation
            recommendations as list containing "Optimize allocation patterns", "Consider memory pooling"
            metadata as dictionary containing
        to bottlenecks
    
    Return bottlenecks

Process called "calculate_leak_suspicion" that takes memory_info as Dictionary returns Float:
    Let allocation_ratio be memory_info.allocation_count divided by (memory_info.allocation_count plus memory_info.deallocation_count)
    Let memory_growth be memory_info.used_memory divided by memory_info.total_memory
    
    Let leak_suspicion be (allocation_ratio plus memory_growth) divided by 2
    Return minimum of leak_suspicion and 1.0

Note: Cache Profiling
Process called "take_cache_profile" that takes context as ProfilingContext returns CacheProfile:
    Let current_time be get_current_time
    Let cache_stats be get_cache_statistics with context as context
    
    Let profile be CacheProfile with:
        timestamp as current_time
        hit_rate as cache_stats.hit_rate
        miss_rate as cache_stats.miss_rate
        eviction_rate as cache_stats.eviction_rate
        compression_ratio as cache_stats.compression_ratio
        cache_size as cache_stats.cache_size
        entry_count as cache_stats.entry_count
        average_access_time as cache_stats.average_access_time
        metadata as dictionary containing
    
    Return profile

Process called "analyze_cache_performance" that takes context as ProfilingContext returns List[BottleneckAnalysis]:
    Let bottlenecks be list containing
    
    If length of context.cache_profiles is less than 2:
        Return bottlenecks
    
    Let cache_trend be analyze_cache_trend with profiles as context.cache_profiles
    
    If cache_trend.average_hit_rate is less than 0.7:
        Add BottleneckAnalysis with:
            bottleneck_type as "cache_miss_rate"
            severity as "high" if cache_trend.average_hit_rate is less than 0.5 else "medium"
            location as "cache"
            impact as 1.0 minus cache_trend.average_hit_rate
            recommendations as list containing "Increase cache size", "Optimize cache key generation", "Review cache eviction policy"
            metadata as dictionary containing
        to bottlenecks
    
    If cache_trend.average_access_time is greater than 0.001:
        Add BottleneckAnalysis with:
            bottleneck_type as "cache_access_time"
            severity as "medium"
            location as "cache"
            impact as cache_trend.average_access_time
            recommendations as list containing "Optimize cache lookup", "Consider cache warming", "Review cache structure"
            metadata as dictionary containing
        to bottlenecks
    
    Return bottlenecks

Note: Compilation Profiling
Process called "record_compilation_profile" that takes context as ProfilingContext and compilation_data as Dictionary returns None:
    Let current_time be get_current_time
    
    Let profile be CompilationProfile with:
        timestamp as current_time
        compilation_time as compilation_data.compilation_time
        optimization_time as compilation_data.optimization_time
        code_generation_time as compilation_data.code_generation_time
        cache_lookup_time as compilation_data.cache_lookup_time
        total_instructions as compilation_data.total_instructions
        optimized_instructions as compilation_data.optimized_instructions
        cache_hits as compilation_data.cache_hits
        cache_misses as compilation_data.cache_misses
        metadata as dictionary containing
    
    Add profile to context.compilation_profiles
    
    If length of context.compilation_profiles is greater than context.config.max_profiling_data:
        Remove context.compilation_profiles at index 0

Process called "analyze_compilation_performance" that takes context as ProfilingContext returns List[BottleneckAnalysis]:
    Let bottlenecks be list containing
    
    If length of context.compilation_profiles is less than 2:
        Return bottlenecks
    
    Let compilation_trend be analyze_compilation_trend with profiles as context.compilation_profiles
    
    If compilation_trend.average_compilation_time is greater than 0.1:
        Add BottleneckAnalysis with:
            bottleneck_type as "compilation_time"
            severity as "high" if compilation_trend.average_compilation_time is greater than 1.0 else "medium"
            location as "compiler"
            impact as compilation_trend.average_compilation_time
            recommendations as list containing "Optimize compilation pipeline", "Increase cache usage", "Review optimization passes"
            metadata as dictionary containing
        to bottlenecks
    
    If compilation_trend.optimization_ratio is less than 0.3:
        Add BottleneckAnalysis with:
            bottleneck_type as "optimization_effectiveness"
            severity as "medium"
            location as "optimizer"
            impact as 1.0 minus compilation_trend.optimization_ratio
            recommendations as list containing "Review optimization passes", "Enable more aggressive optimizations", "Analyze optimization effectiveness"
            metadata as dictionary containing
        to bottlenecks
    
    Return bottlenecks

Note: Runtime Profiling
Process called "record_runtime_profile" that takes context as ProfilingContext and runtime_data as Dictionary returns None:
    Let current_time be get_current_time
    
    Let profile be RuntimeProfile with:
        timestamp as current_time
        execution_time as runtime_data.execution_time
        instruction_count as runtime_data.instruction_count
        branch_count as runtime_data.branch_count
        memory_access_count as runtime_data.memory_access_count
        cache_access_count as runtime_data.cache_access_count
        performance_counters as runtime_data.performance_counters
        metadata as dictionary containing
    
    Add profile to context.runtime_profiles
    
    If length of context.runtime_profiles is greater than context.config.max_profiling_data:
        Remove context.runtime_profiles at index 0

Process called "analyze_runtime_performance" that takes context as ProfilingContext returns List[BottleneckAnalysis]:
    Let bottlenecks be list containing
    
    If length of context.runtime_profiles is less than 2:
        Return bottlenecks
    
    Let runtime_trend be analyze_runtime_trend with profiles as context.runtime_profiles
    
    If runtime_trend.average_execution_time is greater than 0.01:
        Add BottleneckAnalysis with:
            bottleneck_type as "execution_time"
            severity as "high" if runtime_trend.average_execution_time is greater than 0.1 else "medium"
            location as "runtime"
            impact as runtime_trend.average_execution_time
            recommendations as list containing "Optimize hot paths", "Review algorithm complexity", "Consider JIT optimization"
            metadata as dictionary containing
        to bottlenecks
    
    If runtime_trend.branch_misprediction_rate is greater than 0.1:
        Add BottleneckAnalysis with:
            bottleneck_type as "branch_misprediction"
            severity as "medium"
            location as "runtime"
            impact as runtime_trend.branch_misprediction_rate
            recommendations as list containing "Optimize branch patterns", "Use branch prediction hints", "Review control flow"
            metadata as dictionary containing
        to bottlenecks
    
    Return bottlenecks

Note: AI Insights and Analysis
Process called "generate_ai_insights" that takes context as ProfilingContext returns List[PerformanceInsight]:
    Let insights be list containing
    
    Let memory_bottlenecks be analyze_memory_usage with context as context
    Let cache_bottlenecks be analyze_cache_performance with context as context
    Let compilation_bottlenecks be analyze_compilation_performance with context as context
    Let runtime_bottlenecks be analyze_runtime_performance with context as context
    
    For each bottleneck in memory_bottlenecks:
        Add PerformanceInsight with:
            insight_type as "memory_optimization"
            description as "Memory " plus bottleneck.bottleneck_type plus " detected"
            impact_level as bottleneck.severity
            confidence as 0.8
            recommendations as bottleneck.recommendations
            metadata as dictionary containing
        to insights
    
    For each bottleneck in cache_bottlenecks:
        Add PerformanceInsight with:
            insight_type as "cache_optimization"
            description as "Cache " plus bottleneck.bottleneck_type plus " detected"
            impact_level as bottleneck.severity
            confidence as 0.9
            recommendations as bottleneck.recommendations
            metadata as dictionary containing
        to insights
    
    For each bottleneck in compilation_bottlenecks:
        Add PerformanceInsight with:
            insight_type as "compilation_optimization"
            description as "Compilation " plus bottleneck.bottleneck_type plus " detected"
            impact_level as bottleneck.severity
            confidence as 0.85
            recommendations as bottleneck.recommendations
            metadata as dictionary containing
        to insights
    
    For each bottleneck in runtime_bottlenecks:
        Add PerformanceInsight with:
            insight_type as "runtime_optimization"
            description as "Runtime " plus bottleneck.bottleneck_type plus " detected"
            impact_level as bottleneck.severity
            confidence as 0.9
            recommendations as bottleneck.recommendations
            metadata as dictionary containing
        to insights
    
    Return insights

Process called "analyze_profiling_data" that takes context as ProfilingContext returns Dictionary:
    Let analysis be dictionary containing
    
    If length of context.samples is greater than 0:
        Let cpu_trend be analyze_cpu_trend with samples as context.samples
        Let memory_trend be analyze_memory_trend with snapshots as context.memory_snapshots
        Let cache_trend be analyze_cache_trend with profiles as context.cache_profiles
        
        Set analysis["cpu_usage"] to cpu_trend.average_usage
        Set analysis["memory_growth"] to memory_trend.growth_rate
        Set analysis["cache_efficiency"] to cache_trend.average_hit_rate
    
    Return analysis

